    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nIf anyone has tried to update the treesitter parsers with a medium size terminal window, they'll understand the pain.\r\n`:set cmdheight=2 ` is not a desirable solution obviously, if you are not fullscreening the terminal why would you want to get rid of screen real estate.\r\n\r\nSo yeah I think there's a real need for an option to just not read the whole message, I think most people don't want to have the message stuck in the window, specially with the increasing amount of things that spam like 20 messages at the same time.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nProposed solution: something like `:set impatientcmd` or whatever that allows users to opt out of that thing.",
